rComments: The prof replies emails quickly and is great at simplifying material during office hours. However, her lectures can be lengthy, textbook heavy, and monotonous (if you dislike Linguistics). My advice is to drop the course a.s.a.p if you realize you don't like it. LIN is very technical for a Humanities program!

Only take this class if you are serious about entering the Linguistics program.  Do not take it just an an elective. Prof Irimia is very difficult to understand - her accent isn't that bad, but her voice is constantly high then low; very annoying to listen to.  Lectures are copy and pasted straight from the textbook.  Attending class is useless.

Monica cares about her students - she makes sure everyone understands the concepts before moving on, she is very approachable and friendly. Preparing for the test was easy after her lectures! I hardly used the textbook. Great teacher, and really passionate about her subject. Some students were unhappy about her accent... but it's nothing!
